        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We propose to image a dust ring around vMa 2 with ALMA in band 6 using baselines up to 304m. The models in Figure 2 produce total fluxes of 1150 and 430 microJy for thin rings of radii 10 and 20 AU respectively. These correspond to 2.25?? and 4.5?? at a distance of 4.4 pc. With 1?? beams, the worst case scenario (face-on rings) spreads the total signal over 4.5 and 9.0 beams. The mean fluxes per beam are then 250 and 45 microJy respectively. We thus require a sensitivity of 10 microJy per beam for a minimum detection of 4.5 sigma, and the ALMA Observing tool reports this is possible in 6.0 hr. Our OST results are based on the corresponding on-source time of 3.2 hr, in one pointing, and reduced with CLEAN and natural weighting.  
</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We request a correlator set-up that best meets our cold, thermal continuum detection goals in band 6.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Higher angular resolution will spread the weak signal over too many beams.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
